' I don't know.

00:28:14.959 --> 00:28:18.200
But I went over that thing yesterday.

00:28:18.200 --> 00:28:21.689
People were all interested in the puzzle.

00:28:21.689 --> 00:28:25.439
Do you want to show them that before I pray?

00:28:25.439 --> 00:28:33.530
Put in the comment section down below what you think they're trying to say about this picture.

00:28:33.530 --> 00:28:40.730
Do you think it's nothing, or do you feel like there's something to this?

00:28:40.730 --> 00:28:46.053
It's made by the Rockefellers, and I think there's something to it.

00:28:46.053 --> 00:28:47.759
It's not normal.

00:29:03.510 --> 00:29:06.160
I believe they communicate with that.

00:29:06.160 --> 00:29:15.165
If you go back to the Economist main thing every year, they always put out their prediction, and they put one out for 2028.

00:29:23.930 --> 00:29:24.159
That was the one with Xi Jinping and the panda bear.

00:29:24.159 --> 00:29:27.760
This is not normal; this is them communicating.

00:29:27.760 --> 00:29:32.217
The cover this year is interesting to me.

00:29:32.217 --> 00:29:38.994
So you can put in the comment section down below what stands out to you.

00:29:38.994 --> 00:29:42.280
Braden, put the other one up there with the 24.

00:29:42.280 --> 00:29:44.693
Let them look at that for a second.

00:29:44.693 --> 00:29:46.870
Vladimir Putin—I think the swords are interesting.

00:29:46.870 --> 00:29:47.440
All right.

00:29:47.440 --> 00:29:49.630
Well, maybe it's a big nothing burger.

00:29:49.630 --> 00:29:58.684
I try to let you in my little world of things that I think are interesting.

00:29:58.684 --> 00:30:05.120
I've been drinking a ton of water to keep flushing my body.

00:30:05.120 --> 00:30:08.011
I believe that's where we are right now.

00:30:12.847 --> 00:30:14.542
Father, I just thank you, Lord, for another great day today.

00:30:14.542 --> 00:30:17.400
We lift this body up before you.

00:30:17.400 --> 00:30:28.000
We thank you, Father, for all that you've done for us, for anointing us for such a time as this.

00:30:28.000 --> 00:30:37.383
We pray for our president, we pray for the peace of Jerusalem, we pray for our pastors, and we pray for the prophetic.

00:30:37.383 --> 00:30:39.520
We pray for these black swan events.

00:30:54.693 --> 00:30:55.120
We thank you, Father, that you've called us to the kingdom for such a time as this.

00:30:58.811 --> 00:31:00.799
You chose every single one of us—all 4,200 people on here tonight.

00:31:05.131 --> 00:31:05.474
You call us the closers.

00:31:09.539 --> 00:31:13.760
You told me, 'Brandon, there will be a generation that doesn't taste death, and you are that generation.

00:31:13.760 --> 00:31:14.112
' Thank you, Father.

00:31:16.288 --> 00:31:20.114
That means you saved the best for last.

00:31:20.114 --> 00:31:25.488
God, I thank you for all the people that are representing you.

00:31:25.488 --> 00:31:30.827
We have the best of the best prayer warriors on this prayer channel.

00:31:30.827 --> 00:31:41.039
Every single person brings their supply because when we pray together, there's power, for Many hands make light work.

00:31:46.609 --> 00:31:46.840
Father, I thank you for every single person represented here tonight.

00:31:58.019 --> 00:31:58.409
I call them healed and whole and well.

00:31:58.409 --> 00:32:07.671
My wife and I, and my son, we all agree that they are healed and whole and well, and they lack no good thing.

00:32:23.120 --> 00:32:25.232
We lift up this body before you.

00:32:25.584 --> 00:32:33.173
We thank you, Lord, that you were wounded for our transgressions and bruised for our iniquity.

00:32:49.150 --> 00:32:49.540
The chastisement of our peace was upon you, and with your stripes, we are healed.

00:32:54.880 --> 00:32:56.229
This represents so much more than just a little wafer in a cup of juice.

00:32:56.229 --> 00:33:03.980
Jesus paid the price for us to walk in victory over sickness, disease, poverty, lack, and mental torment.

00:33:03.980 --> 00:33:06.346
People are battling depression during this holiday season.

00:33:06.559 --> 00:33:09.760
They feel alone or that they don't have relatives.

00:33:09.760 --> 00:33:13.920
But Father, you said you'd never leave us and you'd never forsake us.

00:33:13.920 --> 00:33:16.489
You're their family during this beautiful holiday season.

00:33:29.279 --> 00:33:29.519
We lift up the people who are alone and we thank you, Father, that they are never alone because you're always with them.

00:33:29.519 --> 00:33:31.129
I pray, Father, for peace.

00:33:48.034 --> 00:33:53.520
You are the Prince of Peace.

00:33:54.160 --> 00:34:03.093
And Father, right now, I ask you to flood their hearts, flood their minds, flood their beings, Father, with your holy, beautiful presence.

00:34:08.513 --> 00:34:13.339
That sweet-smelling fragrance, the fragrance of the Holy Spirit, that peace that passes all understanding.

00:34:13.339 --> 00:34:16.792
Goodness and mercy will follow them all the days of their life.

00:34:16.792 --> 00:34:33.320
Father, if they've lost somebody tragically this year, like Erica—she lost Charlie and their kids are in this first Thanksgiving without having their father there, without having her husband there—and anybody else who lost somebody that's dear to them this year, I thank you, Father, that you fill that void.

00:34:33.320 --> 00:34:38.560
Father, that you are that joy; we find that joy unspeakable and full of glory in these last days.

00:34:38.560 --> 00:34:48.240
Father, I know that days of darkness and days of hardness come, but Father, you said, 'Occupy until I come and enjoy life.

00:34:48.240 --> 00:34:53.299
' Brandon, you tell me all the time, 'Brandon, just enjoy life.

00:34:54.290 --> 00:34:57.008
I want you to have fun and enjoy life.

00:34:57.008 --> 00:35:00.524
Don't look at all the darkness around you.

00:35:00.524 --> 00:35:03.976
Keep vertical and keep your eyes on me in this darkness.

00:35:03.976 --> 00:35:06.860
' And dark times will come; dark times happen.

00:35:14.640 --> 00:35:14.850
But Father, you are my vertical.

00:35:14.850 --> 00:35:19.742
We keep our eyes on you and we don't go horizontal looking all around us.

00:35:19.742 --> 00:35:23.333
We keep our eyes on you.

00:35:23.333 --> 00:35:26.290
We stay the course knowing that you are that peace.

00:35:26.853 --> 00:35:36.811
I pray for every single person right now that has that sense of just that void of depression and anxiety and feeling so lonely.

00:35:36.811 --> 00:35:45.440
We thank you, Lord, that you are that God who brings comfort to the person who needs comfort.

00:35:57.326 --> 00:35:57.714
I believe, Father, that this is the day that they're going to have a turnaround in their emotions, a turnaround in the sadness that they feel.

00:35:59.560 --> 00:36:20.240
And Father, those who are full of joy right now and this is a breeze for them—they love the holidays; the holidays are awesome; they love this time of year—I thank you that you would double the joy on their lives and that, Father, it would flow out of them and spill over to the people who are not having that joyous time.

00:36:20.240 --> 00:36:28.260
Father, you brought joy on every single one of us, that joy unspeakable and full of glory.

00:36:28.260 --> 00:36:45.256
Father, we don't just harbor it in ourselves, but we dump it out on the other people and they see that light and they say, 'There's hope in your eyes.

00:36:45.256 --> 00:36:46.880
There's joy in your eyes.

00:36:46.880 --> 00:36:53.056
' And every single one of us would be that salt and we wouldn't lose our saltiness.

00:36:53.056 --> 00:36:57.392
I thank you, Father, for this beautiful Thanksgiving season that's coming up.

00:36:57.392 --> 00:37:07.420
There's peace in homes and there's no strife around the tables when we eat as families in the days ahead; that you're not bickering and fighting.

00:37:07.420 --> 00:37:18.240
Father, there's peace, and there's not Democrat versus Republican and Catholic against the charismatic; we all get along and they say, 'Man, there's just joy.

00:37:31.520 --> 00:37:31.829
I love being around you.

00:37:31.829 --> 00:37:40.640
' I have to tell myself all the time because I was not a person who liked Christmas for years; in fact, I despised Christmas.

00:37:54.600 --> 00:37:54.800
Not because of Jesus, but because of being around people.

00:37:58.560 --> 00:37:58.880
And I had to say it to myself, 'I love Christmas.

00:37:58.880 --> 00:38:01.200
I love being around folks.

00:38:01.200 --> 00:38:11.154
' I say it all the time; I have to say it to myself all the time.

00:38:11.154 --> 00:38:14.880
I'm just being real with y'all.

00:38:14.880 --> 00:38:18.720
It's something that I've struggled with all the time.

00:38:18.720 --> 00:38:25.189
I used to go around even whenever I was saying, 'I hate the Christmas season.

00:38:25.189 --> 00:38:38.640
' And that may sound really bad, but I'm just telling you something I've had to overcome.

00:38:38.640 --> 00:38:45.771
I say, 'I love the Christmas season.

00:38:45.771 --> 00:38:47.808
I love this timeframe of the year.

00:38:47.808 --> 00:38:50.480
I love the lights.

00:38:50.480 --> 00:38:59.010
' I thank God for Christmas get-togethers at the church or whatever.

00:38:59.010 --> 00:39:12.560
I used to hate that; I used to say it so much and I had what I said, and it's something that I've worked on because Diana loves Christmas.

00:39:12.560 --> 00:39:12.823
Loves it.

00:39:14.920 --> 00:39:15.180
And so do my kids.

00:39:15.180 --> 00:39:17.200
But I just always go...

00:39:17.560 --> 00:39:22.960
and they said, 'Daddy, why do you always say that?

00:39:22.960 --> 00:39:25.886
' I say, 'I don't know.

00:39:34.560 --> 00:39:35.280
I need to work on it.

00:39:35.280 --> 00:39:42.880
' And so I've worked on it; it's something that I love now.

00:39:42.880 --> 00:39:47.490
I go, 'Hey, I love this season.

00:39:47.490 --> 00:39:50.940
' Paisley loves it; it's so wonderful.

00:39:50.940 --> 00:39:55.030
I don't like the materialism of it.

00:39:55.030 --> 00:40:02.870
I think that's where it all started with me as somebody growing up.

00:40:17.084 --> 00:40:17.529
I hate the materialistic side of it, how everybody acts.

00:40:17.529 --> 00:40:32.240
I don't like all of the spending and the debt and the pressure—'Well, you bought me this and I've got to buy you that because if you don't, it's offensive because your gift is not as nice as mine.

00:40:32.240 --> 00:40:37.360
' I don't like that competitive crap and it's why I always was like, 'You know what?

00:40:37.360 --> 00:40:38.928
I don't want to participate in it.

00:40:38.928 --> 00:40:43.539
' So anyone say, 'What you want for Christmas?

00:40:43.539 --> 00:40:44.080
' Nothing.

00:40:44.080 --> 00:40:47.040
I don't want anything.

00:40:59.440 --> 00:40:59.689
And that's the way I always was for a long time.

00:40:59.689 --> 00:41:00.684
'I'll bless you.

00:41:00.684 --> 00:41:02.180
' 'Don't bless me.

00:41:02.180 --> 00:41:04.347
I don't care about it.

00:41:04.347 --> 00:41:11.920
' And that's why there's a lot of people that are similar to being like that.

00:41:11.920 --> 00:41:16.100
So I'm just trying to encourage you.

00:41:16.100 --> 00:41:17.259
Christmas is beautiful.

00:41:17.259 --> 00:41:18.479
It's about Jesus.

00:41:18.479 --> 00:41:20.400
He deserves a day.

00:41:20.400 --> 00:41:22.853
People say, 'Well, it's pagan.

00:41:22.853 --> 00:41:25.920
You're doing this and that.

00:41:25.920 --> 00:41:27.420
' No.

00:41:27.420 --> 00:41:32.453
Jesus deserves a day.

00:41:51.760 --> 00:41:52.053
Jesus deserves a year.

00:41:52.053 --> 00:41:56.230
Jesus deserves everything.

00:41:56.240 --> 00:42:02.380
But if you don't celebrate him at Christmas, celebrate him sometime.

00:42:02.380 --> 00:42:03.260
He deserves it.

00:42:03.260 --> 00:42:05.787
That's what I told my kids.

00:42:10.176 --> 00:42:10.400
We make him a big Christmas cake and write 'Happy Birthday' on it.

00:42:11.072 --> 00:42:15.051
We even allowed you all to be a part of that last year.

00:42:36.120 --> 00:42:43.067
We celebrated and had a cake and did it all.

00:42:43.067 --> 00:42:46.204
We show you what we do as a family.

00:42:46.204 --> 00:42:51.219
We make it about Jesus being the reason for the season.

00:43:12.267 --> 00:43:12.613
And all of this—all the materialism, all Black Friday, and all the hype—I keep Jesus the main thing.

00:43:28.019 --> 00:43:28.439
I refuse to rob him of it and let Santa Claus take the glory.

00:43:28.439 --> 00:43:32.592
Santa Claus isn't coming to my house.

00:43:32.592 --> 00:43:38.041
I'm always saying Santa Claus doesn't exist in this house.

00:43:38.041 --> 00:43:40.163
Jesus does.

00:43:40.163 --> 00:43:41.792
He's the provider.

00:43:41.792 --> 00:43:48.090
There isn't a man in a red suit.

00:43:48.090 --> 00:43:50.400
Jesus provides for my kids.

00:43:50.400 --> 00:44:02.560
I never let someone take the glory other than Jesus Christ; he gets all the glory in my house.

00:44:08.879 --> 00:44:09.119
And we've raised our kids that way.

00:44:09.119 --> 00:44:16.587
Jesus is the reason for this season, not some big guy in a red suit.

00:44:16.587 --> 00:44:22.693
It's fun, okay, a fairy tale, whatever you want to say, but Jesus is the reason.

00:44:22.693 --> 00:44:26.594
He is the reason for our season.

00:44:31.306 --> 00:44:31.613
And we give him all the glory, honor, and praise.

00:44:37.050 --> 00:44:41.730
And we give him a birthday cake; he may not eat it in the natural, but we celebrate with him like he's there.

00:44:46.684 --> 00:44:46.862
And we have video showing you what we do.

00:44:46.862 --> 00:44:48.779
It's all glory to Jesus.

00:44:50.139 --> 00:44:53.622
We always give the glory to Jesus in this beautiful season.

00:44:59.040 --> 00:44:59.508
And now we give you praise and thanksgiving.

00:45:00.445 --> 00:45:09.119
You are so real to us, and when you get real with God, God will become real to you.

00:45:14.600 --> 00:45:18.440
We make sure we always keep the main thing the main thing.

00:45:33.166 --> 00:45:33.851
Jesus is important in our home.

00:45:33.851 --> 00:45:36.594
Jesus is provider.

00:45:36.594 --> 00:45:38.613
Jesus is our healer.

00:45:38.613 --> 00:45:40.879
Jesus is our comforter.

00:45:46.680 --> 00:45:47.040
You got that there, babe?

00:45:47.040 --> 00:45:48.275
There it is.

00:45:48.275 --> 00:45:49.048
Merry Christmas.

00:45:49.048 --> 00:45:50.703
Brownies or cookies or something.

00:45:50.703 --> 00:45:52.549
And so this year, Diana found it.

00:45:52.549 --> 00:45:52.937
Happy?

00:45:52.937 --> 00:45:56.836
Did you see it?

00:46:11.279 --> 00:46:11.680
Yeah.

00:46:11.680 --> 00:46:12.880
It's important.

00:46:12.880 --> 00:46:13.880
It's so important.

00:46:17.920 --> 00:46:18.120
Thank you, Father.

00:46:18.120 --> 00:46:22.096
Thank you, Father, for what you did for this household this year.

00:46:22.096 --> 00:46:34.560
As we close out 2025, thank you that we are thriving and we come alive and all the things you can say to rhyme with it.

00:46:34.560 --> 00:46:39.908
Everything that was is what you've done for us and we're so grateful.

00:46:39.908 --> 00:46:44.000
We're so healed and whole and well—mentally, emotionally, physically, financially.

00:46:44.000 --> 00:46:48.352
You have been good to Brandon and Diana, and my children.

00:46:48.352 --> 00:46:50.128
We praise you, Father.

00:46:50.128 --> 00:46:57.050
We thank you, Lord, for 2025 as we have a day of thanksgiving coming.

00:46:57.050 --> 00:47:04.538
We take this body right now in Jesus' name.

00:47:05.576 --> 00:47:09.400
I know it was different, but it's just from the heart.

00:47:09.400 --> 00:47:12.559
People make things so religious.

00:47:12.559 --> 00:47:19.699
Get real with God; he will become real to you.

00:47:19.699 --> 00:47:22.810
Stop treating him like he's untouchable.

00:47:28.811 --> 00:47:29.097
He wants you to sit in his lap.

00:47:29.097 --> 00:47:36.560
Jesus made it possible for you to sit with him in the heavenlies and take the blood of Jesus.

00:47:36.560 --> 00:47:40.011
What represents the blood is what makes it that way.

00:47:43.988 --> 00:47:54.910
Thank you, Jesus, for your blood, because if it wasn't for you, who eradicated sin and got rid of it all, I would be in so much trouble.

00:47:54.910 --> 00:48:00.880
We would all have to sacrifice a bull, and the vegans would really hate it.

00:48:00.880 --> 00:48:09.006
What would you do then if we still had to sacrifice a goat or a sheep for sin or whatever?

00:48:09.006 --> 00:48:17.639
They'd be saying, 'Oh my God, what would you do?

00:48:17.639 --> 00:48:21.714
What would you vegans do then?

00:48:21.714 --> 00:48:27.784
' You're in trouble because you won't even eat it.

00:48:27.784 --> 00:48:39.108
So now you've got a cat killer for your sin.

00:49:01.119 --> 00:49:01.535
Thank Jesus even more for his blood, vegans.

00:49:01.535 --> 00:49:03.200
I'm just saying.

00:49:03.200 --> 00:49:07.466
I'm not trying to be funny.

00:49:07.466 --> 00:49:09.319
It's serious, y'all.

00:49:21.794 --> 00:49:22.400
You know, the tree huggers would hate it, but Jesus paid the price for you to walk in victory.

00:49:27.000 --> 00:49:27.333
And we don't have to kill any goats or bulls and all those things.

00:49:38.033 --> 00:49:42.800
Look what he did for us.

00:49:42.800 --> 00:49:48.149
There is so much to be thankful for.

00:49:53.920 --> 00:49:58.044
We take the blood, and we say we make much of the blood, and the blood makes much of us.

00:50:10.373 --> 00:50:11.866
Thank you, Lord, that we don't have to kill a goat or all this because you were the lamb slain from the foundation.

00:50:11.866 --> 00:50:13.508
You did it all.

00:50:13.508 --> 00:50:19.017
Jesus paid it all; all to him I owe.

00:50:38.343 --> 00:50:38.720
Thank you, Father.

00:50:38.720 --> 00:50:39.626
Thank you, Father.

00:50:39.626 --> 00:50:47.280
We praise the one who paid my debt and raises life up from the dead.

00:50:47.280 --> 00:50:50.079
I believe, Father, for the blood.

00:50:50.079 --> 00:50:58.160
I believe, Father, for what you did for us.

00:50:58.160 --> 00:51:03.947
You've been so good to us in Jesus' mighty name.

00:51:03.947 --> 00:51:04.960
Amen.

00:51:04.960 --> 00:51:05.973
Amen.

00:51:17.542 --> 00:51:18.810
Thank you, Lord.

00:51:18.810 --> 00:51:24.537
That's why I just try to be real with the Lord.

00:51:24.537 --> 00:51:29.165
You know, I tick a lot of religious people off.

00:51:29.165 --> 00:51:30.079
Good.

00:51:30.079 --> 00:51:47.760
I want to be able to go into the synagogue and flip the tables and say we have to be real with him.

00:51:47.760 --> 00:51:51.863
You've got to be real with Jesus.

00:51:51.863 --> 00:51:54.759
Stop being so flaky.

00:51:54.759 --> 00:52:02.663
Lord, I plead the blood over my eyes.

00:52:02.663 --> 00:52:07.340
If you want to show me anything, fine.

00:52:07.340 --> 00:52:09.387
If you don't, it's good, too.

00:52:09.387 --> 00:52:10.503
But we're here.

00:52:15.670 --> 00:52:15.892
And Lord, we pray over the things you showed us last time.

00:52:15.892 --> 00:52:30.319
Father, I don't even really truly know how to pray over all of that because it was so much in the natural of my natural tongue.

00:52:30.319 --> 00:52:34.913
But I pray in the spirit, and I lift up this war before you.

00:52:35.062 --> 00:52:36.906
I lift it up before you, Father.

00:52:36.906 --> 00:52:41.466
There are so many people losing their lives.

00:52:41.466 --> 00:52:46.222
They said an average of 10,000 people a day.

00:52:46.222 --> 00:52:47.839
Is that 70,000 a week?

00:52:58.560 --> 00:52:58.780
That is an astronomical amount of men and women dying on both sides.

00:52:58.780 --> 00:53:03.920
Lord, this has been going on for years.

00:53:03.920 --> 00:53:08.777
Lord, I thank you.

00:53:08.777 --> 00:53:27.333
No matter how many people and these big businessmen who are involved in this and these evil people who are trying to escalate war, I ask you, Father, to put a stop to the war.

00:53:27.333 --> 00:53:30.719
Help us, Holy Spirit.

00:53:30.719 --> 00:53:39.790
Work on the behalf that Zelensky would be removed, that this government would be put in, and that they would bring peace to Ukraine.

00:53:39.790 --> 00:53:45.474
The Ukrainian people would have peace and stop having all the bloodshed; they're precious to you and precious in your sight.

00:53:45.474 --> 00:53:47.371
The same with the Russians.

00:53:47.371 --> 00:53:52.999
We pray over every Russian representative here who has lost people just like the Ukrainians.

00:53:55.200 --> 00:54:00.810
And you know, they're not fighting a war for themselves; they're fighting because they've been told they have to.

00:54:02.690 --> 00:54:04.400
And I thank you, Father, that there's peace even in Ukraine.

00:54:04.880 --> 00:54:06.845
There's peace in Russia.

00:54:06.845 --> 00:54:08.630
There's peace, Father.

00:54:16.899 --> 00:54:17.189
And that this would stop.

00:54:21.839 --> 00:54:22.148
The escalation of things would stop.

00:54:26.696 --> 00:54:26.912
That Ukraine would back down and not want to join NATO.

00:54:26.912 --> 00:54:32.525
Whatever it is that is causing this fire to burn so bright.

00:54:32.525 --> 00:54:41.759
We know we're in the end times, and you said we'd have wars and rumors of wars, but God, we still pray for peace.

00:54:41.759 --> 00:54:43.809
We still pray for peace.

